Senate Education 1
Amendment No. 1 to SB2485
White
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2485* House Bill No. 2410
by deleting subsection (b) in Section 1 and substituting:
(b) An LEA or public charter school shall not use a video camera surveillance
system to continuously monitor students, teachers, and staff in a special education
classroom unless:
(1) All teachers and staff that provide special education or related
services in the special education classroom consent, in writing, to being
continuously monitored using the system while they are providing special
education or related services in the special education classroom; and
(2) The parents of a majority of the students assigned to receive special
education or related services in the special education classroom consent, in
writing, to the parent's student being continuously monitored using the system
while they are receiving special education or related services in the special
education classroom.
AND FURTHER AMEND by designating subsection (f) in Section 1 as subsection (g) and
adding the following as a new subsection (f):
SA0792
016123
- 1 -

(f) If the parent of a student assigned to receive special education or related
services in the special education classroom in which a video camera surveillance system
has been installed does not consent, in writing, to the parent's student being
continuously monitored using the system while the parent's student is receiving special
education or related services in the special education classroom, then the LEA or public
charter school shall not use, refer to, or rely on any photograph or recording made using
the video camera surveillance system that features the nonconsenting parent's student
for any purpose, including, but not limited to, the discipline, assignment, or placement of
the nonconsenting parent's student.
